M1 Meghalaya Portal - Project Explanation

Sir, basically I have worked on multiple projects, but currently I am working on the M1 Meghalaya Portal, which is a Government project for the Meghalaya State Government.

In this project, my role is Full Stack Developer.

Frontend: Angular
Backend: Node.js (Express.js)
Database: PostgreSQL
Project Objective

The main objective of this project is to provide a single-window platform where citizens can apply for different government schemes and government officers can manage the complete approval process digitally.

The project has three major portals:

Citizen Portal
Department Portal
admin portal

1. Citizen Portal
The citizen portal is used by citizens to register and apply for government schemes.
Citizen Registration
Citizens can register using:
PDS (Ration Card)
EPIC ID (Voter ID)

During registration, we perform multiple validations and family-linking verification to ensure the citizen data is correct.
After successful registration, a unique Member ID is generated for the citizen.
Then the citizen can log in to the portal and access various government schemes.

Scheme Applications
Citizens can apply for multiple schemes such as:
Homestay Scheme
Chief Minister Scholarship Scheme
Welfare Schemes
Other government services

On their dashboard, citizens can track the status of their applications, such as:
Draft
Pending
Approved
Rejected

This gives complete visibility of their applications.

2. Department Portal
The department portal is used by government officers to process scheme applications.
Hierarchy-Based Workflow
Once a citizen submits an application, it goes through different levels of government officers.

For example:
Nodal Officer
DEO (Data Entry Operator)
District Officer
IAS Officer
Secretary Level Officers

Each officer has specific roles and permissions.
They review applications, verify documents, approve or reject requests, and forward files to the next level.
Different Workflow for Different Schemes
Every government scheme has its own approval process.

Dashboards and Reports
I have also worked on dashboards and reports where officers can monitor:

Total applications
Pending applications
Approved applications
Rejected applications
Scheme-wise statistics

This helps departments track their daily operations efficiently.

