Sir, one of the important projects I worked on is CM Connect VDV, which is a Government of Meghalaya project. In this project, my role is Full Stack Developer. We are using Angular for frontend, Node.js for backend, PostgreSQL as database, and IndexedDB with Dexie.js for offline storage.

The main purpose of this project is to help Village Data Volunteers (VDVs) collect citizen information and conduct surveys in villages. These VDVs visit remote villages and help citizens access government schemes.

Since many villages in Meghalaya have poor internet connectivity, this is an offline-first application.

The project has two portals:

1. VDV Portal

This portal is used by field workers (VDVs).

When a VDV logs in for the first time, they perform a sync process. During sync, all required data such as citizen data, survey forms, and scheme-related information is downloaded from the server and stored in IndexedDB.

After that, the VDV can work completely offline.

VDVs visit villages throughout the day and fill different survey and service forms for citizens. I developed more than 25 survey and service forms for different government schemes.

All data is stored locally in IndexedDB while working offline.

Whenever internet becomes available, the VDV performs sync again and all locally stored forms are uploaded to the main server database.

I also worked on:

Offline data storage using IndexedDB and Dexie.js
Data synchronization process
Conflict handling during sync
Geolocation tracking during village visits
Attendance tracking for VDVs
2. DCS Admin Portal

This portal is used by government officers and administrators.

Through this portal, officers can:

Monitor VDV activities
View submitted surveys
Track attendance
Check village visit reports
View dashboards and reports
Take action based on collected survey data

Since VDVs receive incentives for field visits and completed work, the admin portal is also used to track their performance and verify their activities.









